<header>
    Discover Tochigi Prefecture, Japan
</header>

<div class="content">

    <!-- Museums Section -->
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Tochigi Prefecture Museums</h2>
        <div class="text-box">
            <p>Tochigi boasts a variety of museums that highlight the area's history, art, and culture. Notable museums include the Tochigi Prefectural Museum of Fine Arts, which showcases both traditional and contemporary Japanese artwork, and the Nikko Toshogu Museum, dedicated to the famous Nikko Toshogu Shrine.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Nature Walks Section -->
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Nature Walks in Tochigi</h2>
        <div class="text-box">
            <p>Tochigi is home to scenic natural landscapes perfect for hiking and nature walks. Explore the breathtaking hills around Nikko National Park, or take a peaceful stroll along the Kinugawa River. The area's lush forests and mountainous terrain are ideal for outdoor lovers.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Shrines Section -->
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Shinto & Buddhist Shrines</h2>
        <div class="text-box">
            <p>Tochigi is home to many historical Shinto and Buddhist shrines, including the Nikko Toshogu Shrine, a UNESCO World Heritage Site dedicated to Tokugawa Ieyasu, and Futarasan Shrine, which offers a serene and spiritual experience. These sacred places attract visitors with their beautiful architecture and tranquil surroundings.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Food Section -->
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Tochigi Cuisine</h2>
        <div class="text-box">
            <p>Tochigi is known for its delicious and unique food offerings. Don't miss Tochigi's famous Yuba (tofu skin) and local specialties like strawberry-based desserts, including the region's famous "Tochigi strawberries". Traditional Japanese sweets like mochi and sushi are also widely enjoyed in the prefecture.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Traditional Activities Section -->
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Traditional Activities in Tochigi</h2>
        <div class="text-box">
            <p>Experience traditional Japanese arts in Tochigi, such as the ancient art of Ikebana (flower arranging), tea ceremonies, and the rhythmic drumming of Taiko performances. Participate in local festivals like the Nikko Toshogu Shrine Grand Festival, where you can see the rich cultural heritage of Tochigi come to life.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

